  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tigray Crisis: Emergency Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) Response for Refugees in Eastern Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Due to the large influx of refugees into Gedaref in Eastern Sudan, the risk of disease outbreaks and their spread in the refugee camps and within hosting communities are high. The overall objective of this project is to reduce the risk of water-borne diseases and improve access to sanitation and hygiene services for populations affected by conflict and disaster in Gedaref. Given the needs assessed on the ground, a special focus is being given on the strategic implementation of permanent sanitation facilities coupled with the preposition of basic hygiene items. This is being achieved through a tailor-made sanitation and hygiene promotion package which strictly revolves around the timely construction of permanent latrines and showers coupled with the prepositioning soap. The response will also include flood preparedness and response to water-borne disease outbreaks through the preposition and distribution of soap in Um Rakuba and Tunaydibah camps.</narrative>
  </description>
